  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.3All Creatio products\nOn this page\nTo work with additional information in Creatio, use the **Attachments** component.\nUse the component to store external files. The component is available on some record pages, for example, contact pages.\nThe **Attachments** component has the following views available:\n* **Gallery** view. In this view, the files and links added to the detail are displayed as tiles. The tile appearance varies depending on the file extension.\nFig. 1 Gallery view\n![Fig.\u00a01 Gallery view](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Platform_basics/work_with_attachments/scr_gallery_attachment.png)\n* **List** view. In this view, the files and links added to the detail are displayed as a list of records.\nFig. 2 List view\n![Fig.\u00a02 List view](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Platform_basics/work_with_attachments/scr_list_attachment.png)\n## Attach files to records\u200b\n1. **Open** the needed record, for example, the task page.\n2. **Click** the **Attachments** button.\n3. Click ![btn_upload.png](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Platform_basics/work_with_attachments/btn_upload.png). You can also drag the file and drop it into the component (Fig. 3).\nFig. 3 Drag a file into the Attachments component\n![Fig.\u00a03 Drag a file into the Attachments component](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Platform_basics/work_with_attachments/scr_upload_file.png)\n**As a result** , Creatio will save the selected file in the component.\n## Download attachments\u200b\nTo download the file added to the **Attachments** component, click its name. The browser will save it to its downloads folder.\n## Delete attachments\u200b\nTo delete an attachment, click ![btn_more.png](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Platform_basics/work_with_attachments/btn_more.png) next to the file \u2192 **Delete**.\nCreatio also deletes attachments automatically when a record is deleted. Out of the box, attachments are deleted from the \"Uploaded file\" database table 2 days after the record is removed. You can adjust this delay using the \"File deletion delay period, days\" (`FileDeletionDelayPeriod` code) system setting. Learn more: [Manage system settings](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=269).\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Get started with Creatio Freedom UI](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2445)",
